Adapted skills carry an attribution line stating that the file was modified.
Skills written from scratch by The Balanced Investor Club carry none, because
they are not derived from anything.

Modifications by The Balanced Investor Club:

- Re-scoped, not re-badged. The upstream catalogue serves bankers, private-equity
  analysts and fund administrators. This one serves a person trying to understand
  a company. The workflows that presuppose a client book, a data room or an
  investment committee were removed; the ones that stayed had their audience
  changed, and with it the object of the skill.

- The sell-side rating apparatus was removed entirely: ratings, price targets,
  implied upside, and the quality gates that required them. Where a verdict would
  sit, deliverables now carry the implied value range, its sensitivity, and what
  would prove the read wrong.

- Data connectors replaced with The Balanced Investor Club MCP connector.
  Web search for market data is prohibited throughout.

- Skills written from scratch, not adapted: trade-log, journal-mirror,
  stock-tracker, mood-regime, screener, macro-read, dividends, reverse-dcf,
  ownership-context, transcript-vs-numbers.

- The educational framing and disclaimer moved from the bottom of each SKILL.md
  — where the model read them and no reader ever saw them — into the generated
  document itself, defined once in OUTPUT-BLOCK.md and referenced everywhere.

- A verifier added (scripts/verify-skill.sh) and wired into CI. A rule that
  nothing enforces gets followed about eleven percent of the time; we measured it.
